President Obama issued a statement expressing gratitude for Chairwoman Debbie Wasserman Schultz's leadership of the DNC over the past eight years. He praised her for bringing Democrats together and supporting their shared goals, including economic recovery, social and civil justice, and healthcare for all Americans. The President highlighted Wasserman Schultz's fundraising and organizing skills, as well as her passion, commitment, and warmth. He also acknowledged her dedication to serving her constituents in Congress and expressed his gratitude for her efforts. President Obama stated that Wasserman Schultz will continue to serve as a member of Congress from Florida and will always be a dear friend.